parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to stop the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has to be pumped to stop the vehicle
and the vehicle fails to stop immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the vehicle's brakes lock up
the vehicle jerks or vibrates when braking
and the brake pedal feels hard or stiff.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Fluid and Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake fluid is contaminated
the brake lines are damaged
the brake master cylinder fails
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a potential safety issue, and may prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
flashing
or stays on; the passenger airbag sensor is faulty; the airbag system is malfunctioning; the airbag light does not turn off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the battery and brake lights illuminate on the dashboard
the vehicle may not start
and the electrical system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the passenger seat sensor light flashes
and the airbag system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The electrical system malfunctions
the battery and brake lights illuminate on the dashboard
the vehicle may not start
and the vehicle's systems may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The brake pedal extends to the floorboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
